@node "key" "The keyfile"

  The Keyfile is file which must be copied to devs:. With the keyfile are the
  disabled @{"options" link "option"} useable and you have automatically the full version
  of the dA cOOL bOOTER, logical!

  You get the keyfile when you send US$15 or 20DM and the filled in
  @{"Registration form" link "register"} to @{"me" link "autor"}.
 
  You aren`t than allowed to spread the keyfile! In the keyfile is you`re
  complete adress saved. Spreaded keyfiles are an act of software piracy!

@endnode

@node "wasmacht" ""

  dA cOOL bOOTER (DCB) starts all games/demos which need all the
  chip memory (Capital Punishment, Switchback...) from workbench.
  Additionally it forces ECS games/demos to run on AGA
  (e.g. the Monkeys, Red Baron...)

  In the unregistered version you can only start the games/demos
  with the help of the GUI. With the registered version, you`re
  able to get a starter in the game/demo dir installed,
  which you must simple doubleclick.
  
  Starting a game/demo is as easy as possible.
  See how @{"easy" link "ques"} it is.
@endnode

@node "Copyright" "Copyright"

  Da Cool Booter is copyrighted 1997 by Andreas Falkenhahn.

  Da Cool Booter  without the Keyfile in devs: can be copied. Copying the
  keyfile illegal.    
  
  This program is @{"Shareware" link "cardware"}. If you use it and enjoy it please
  @{"register" link "register"} yourself and get post hastes the @{"full version" link "option"}.
  To register, please fill in the @{"Registration form" link "register"}, print it and send it to @{"me" link "autor"}.

  The version without keyfile can be identified by the requester at start
  can (shall) be copied from everyone.
 
  Da Cool Booter shan`t be selled for more than $2. If you have bought it
  for more, please change your dealer fast.
  
  Da Cool Booter must distributed with all files on the disk apart from
  devs:DaCoolBooter.key, of course. Please spread it not as an DMS Archive, only
  as a disk or LHA/LZX archive. 

  I don`t accede any liability if Da Cool Booter has something damaged. It
  was compfortable @{"tested" link "Autor"} and at me nothing dangerous happened. 
 
@endnode

